<p>If a portfolio earns 8% nominal but inflation runs at 5%, the investor is not compounding at 8% in any meaningful lifestyle sense. Real wealth is growing closer to 3%. That is the number that matters for retirement withdrawals, endowment spending, and long-horizon saving targets.</p>
